This file holds indentation test cases that are known-broken and are NOT
run by the test suite (nothing references this file from roc-ts-mode-test.el).

These blocks used to live in roc-ts-mode-examples.erts marked "Skip: t".
They were moved here for two reasons:

1. They were written against a previous tree-sitter-roc grammar / an older
   era of Roc syntax, and the mode does not indent them correctly yet.

2. Emacs 30.1's `ert-test-erts-file' mis-parses "Skip: t" blocks: the skip
   path in `ert-test--erts-test' consumes the closing "=-=-=" delimiter,
   but the caller then searches for that same delimiter again. As a result
   every skipped block silently disables the test that follows it, and a
   skipped block at the end of the file aborts the whole run with a
   search-failed error. (This is what made the erts suite fail wholesale
   while or-pattern2 sat at the end of the examples file.)

To revive one of these cases, fix the indentation behavior it documents and
move the block back into roc-ts-mode-examples.erts WITHOUT a "Skip: t" line.

Name: with-comments
Skip: t
=-=
app [main!] { pf: platform "https://github.com/roc-lang/basic-cli/releases/download/0.20.0/X73hGh05nNTkDHU06FHC0YfFaQB1pimX7gncRcao5mU.tar.br" }

import pf.Stdout
import pf.Task

# this is a comment
main! = |_args| {
	# second comment
	z = "hi"
	# third comment
	obj = 
	# fourth comment
		{ a: "hi\n" }
	q = obj.a
	Stdout.line!("hi")
}
=-=-=

Name: split-lines-2
Skip: t
=-=
app [
	main,
] {
	pf: platform "https://github.com/roc-lang/basic-cli/releases/download/0.20.0/X73hGh05nNTkDHU06FHC0YfFaQB1pimX7gncRcao5mU.tar.br",
}

import pf.Stdout
import pf.Task

main :
	Int(
		q,
		zib,
	),
	Int(
		qq,
		{
			a : Int,
			b : Int(_) => Int,
		},
	) ->
		[
			False(
				(
					Int(
						qqq,
					) ->
						zabl),
					),
		]
main! = |_args| {
	z = "hi"
	obj = 
		{ a: "hi\n" }
	q = obj.a
	Stdout.line!("hi")
}
=-=-=

Name: or-pattern2
Skip: t
=-=
app [main!] { pf: platform "https://github.com/roc-lang/basic-cli/releases/download/0.20.0/X73hGh05nNTkDHU06FHC0YfFaQB1pimX7gncRcao5mU.tar.br" }

f : Something -> Something
f = |z| match List.get(nfa, state_ind) {
	Ok(A(b, c)) => A(c, b)
	Ok(_)
	| Ok(_)
	| Err(_) =>
		Ok(32)
	}
=-=-=
